  • Straps are load rated with the correct thickness and number of fasteners, in contrast with field-fabricated straps

  • Loads have been increased for wind and seismic forces

  • Floor-to-floor clear span application

The MSTA is designed to resist tension loads in wood-to-wood uplift applications. This medium strap tie utilizes a staggered nail pattern to help minimize wood splitting. The MSTA is designed for use on the edge of 2x members.

  • Straps are load rated with the correct thickness and number of fasteners, in contrast with field-fabricated straps

  • Loads have been increased for wind and seismic forces

  • Floor-to-floor clear span application

  • For use on the edge of 2x members

  • Length: 36-in

  • Width: 1-1/4-in

  • Made from 16-gauge steel

  • ZMAX galvanization offers extra corrosion resistance for exterior and treated-wood applications

  • Install with 10d common nails or #9 x 1-1/2-in Strong-Drive SD screws
